The crew here is great and where the food is concerned...well it's a pretty standard taco bell. The problem is that it's the most expensive Taco Bell in the country.  The prices here are on average 2x-3x higher than at any other location in the nation. I travel frequently and TB is my favorite fast food restaurant.  Here a spicy tostada will run you $2.72 after tax vs $1+ tax on the Vegas Strip (a Cantina location) vs $1.35+ tax in the Miami Airport location.  A double decker supreme here is between $4-$5 vs $2-$2.39 and the list goes on.  Even the meal deals are over priced.  Why price gouge in a predominantly Dominican neighborhood?  If you can, go to Union Square or Penn Station instead where they're a bit more reasonable. If you can't, you'll do better taking your cash to the grocery store and making your own tacos at home.
